  h2 Case Study<br/>Sorba Atlanta
  hr.faded-hr
  figure
    blockquote Ian anticipated our needs at every stage and gave our site new features and a great design.
    figcaption ~ Brett Davidson, <em>President of SORBA Atlanta</em>
  h3 Discover
  p Initially, Brett wanted a straight redesign. The site is essentially a blogging platform for their organization and he wanted it looking good.
  p As we went through the discovery phase, we <strong>identified our primary goals</strong> as unifying the look and feel of the brand across platforms, allowing <strong>easy updates through Wordpress</strong>, enhancing usability through restructuring of information, increasing awareness of the organization, generating mobile traffic by making the site <strong>responsive</strong>, boosting direct traffic, attracting repeat visitors, and <strong>generating donations</strong> and new membership.
  h3 Concept and Design
  p I began taking a close look at the sites of other Sorba chapters, trying to glean what information was most important to Sorba members. It turned out to be trail status - mountain bikers want to know if they can ride. I also wanted draw attention to the donate button and keep the homepage fresh by featuring recent blog posts.
  p I provided Brett with a couple of style tiles - small, flexible documents to <strong>communicate the visual evolution of the brand</strong>.
